        The dietary assessment forms were extensive.

        Holloway announced via fruiting bodies arranged around the medical chamber:
        "Section One: Basic Nutritional Requirements. Daily caloric intake range?"

        Kira's stomach growled loud enough that Scout bounced anxiously.

        Kira said — "Approximately two thousand calories per day for baseline maintenance."

        Holloway asked: "Excellent! Macronutrient ratios?"

        Kira rubbed her face. "I don't… Balanced — carbohydrates, proteins, fats — the usual human stuff."

        Holloway asked: "Could you be more specific?"

        Kira said — "Forty percent carbs, thirty percent protein, thirty percent fat. Roughly. I'm a cargo specialist, not a nutritionist."

        Holloway said: "Noted! Buddy, can you provide more detailed nutritional data from Kira's medical file?"

        Buddy said: "Accessing records now. Kira's optimal nutritional profile includes complete proteins with essential amino acids, complex carbohydrates, essential fatty acids, and a comprehensive vitamin and mineral panel. Shall I list each micronutrient requirement?"

        Holloway said: "Please do!"

        This was going to take forever.

        Mushrooms were fruiting throughout the chamber — Remedy's network responding to the discussion. The robot stood to one side, observing.

        Remedy said — "While we document requirements, I'm analyzing which compounds I can synthesize from available plant chemistry. Proteins are possible — I can fruit mushrooms with complete amino acid profiles. Carbohydrates, easy. Some fats. Vitamins will be… challenging."

        Kira asked: "How challenging?"

        Remedy said: "Vitamin B twelve might be impossible. Some others I can approximate through fungal compounds, but they won't be identical to what you're used to."

        Great. Alien vitamin deficiency to look forward to.

        Holloway continued via the fruiting bodies: "Section Two: Dietary Restrictions. Do you follow any religious or cultural dietary guidelines?"

        Kira stared at the fruiting body. "Are you serious?"

        Holloway said: "Dietary preferences are very important for individual wellness!"

        Kira said — "I crashed on an alien planet — my ship exploded. I'll eat whatever won't kill me."

        Holloway said: "I understand you're in unusual circumstances, but we want to respect cultural practices — for example: kosher requirements? Halal guidelines? Vegetarian preferences?"

        Her stomach made a sound like dying machinery.

        Kira said: "No religious restrictions. No cultural requirements. No vegetarian preferences. I will eat *literally anything edible*."

        Holloway said: "Wonderful! Very flexible dietary parameters. Next: favorite cuisines or flavor profiles?"

        Scout bumped against her leg sympathetically.

        Kira said: "You're asking my favorite cuisines while I haven't eaten in thirty-six hours."

        Holloway said: "Context helps us provide optimal nutrition!"

        Kira said: "My favorite cuisine is _food_ — any and all food."

        Buddy said — "Kira's consumption history suggests preference for protein-rich meals, minimal processed sugars, occasional chocolate as treat food. Spice tolerance: moderate."
      </text>
