        Kira nodded, still eating — she couldn't talk; she was too busy desperately shoveling mushroom paste into her face.

        Holloway said, "Excellent adaptation to a novel food source! Your flexibility is commendable!"

        She wasn't being flexible — she was starving, but whatever.

        The container emptied faster than dignity allowed.

        Kira sat back, finally full — or at least… not actively dying of hunger. She was exhausted, overwhelmed — but fed.

        Kira said, "Thank you — to Remedy, to Holloway, to Scout who stayed with me through hours of forms and testing. Seriously — thank you."

        Remedy said, "Chemistry works — humans need specific molecules. I can provide those molecules through fungal synthesis. Not perfect, but functional."

        Functional was good enough. And it was — perfect didn't matter. She had food now, a way to keep eating. Basic survival established.

        One more impossible thing adapted to, one more absurd requirement navigated.

        She was learning to survive here — through forms, through testing, through mushroom paste that tasted like despair.

        ¶

        But surviving nonetheless.
